text: The Kansas River, also known as the Kaw, is a river in northeastern Kansas in the United States. ==Places and locations along the river== ===Counties=== * Wyandotte and Johnson (boundary in part) * Jefferson and Douglas (boundary) * Shawnee * Pottawatomie and Wabaunsee (boundary) * Riley * Geary * Jewell == References == ==Other websites== * Bowersock Mills & Power Company * Kaw Point * Kaw Valley Heritage Alliance * USGS * Lower Kansas * USGS: Map of Historical and Cultural Sites along the Kaw Valley Category:Rivers of Kansas Category:Bodies of water of Douglas County, Kansas
